<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(v) Offset Credit Value_Dollar value credits awarded by international customer's offset agency including any intangible
factors/multipliers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Actual Offset Value_ Dollar value of the offset transaction without multipliers/intangible factors. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Description of Offset Product/Service_Short description of the type of offset (e.g., coproduction, technology
transfer, subcontract activity, training, purchase, cash payment, etc.). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(viii) Broad Industry Category_Broad classification of the industry in which the offset transaction was fulfilled
(e.g., aerospace, electronics, chemicals, industrial machinery, textiles, etc.). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ix) Direct or Indirect Offset_Specify whether the offset transaction was a direct offset (defined as any product
or service directly related to the defense systems procured/sold) or indirect (any other transactions). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(x) Name of Country in Which Offset Was Fulfilled_United States, purchasing country, or third country. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Offset transactions of the same type (same fulfilling entity, receiving entity, and offset product/service)
completed during the same reporting period may be combined. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Reporting on offset agreements entered into. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) In addition to the itemized list of offset transactions completed during the year as specified in paragraph (d)
of this section, U.S. firms should provide information regarding new offset agreements entered into during the year,
including the following elements: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Name of Country_Country of entity purchasing the weapon system, defense item, or service subject to offset; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Name or Description of Weapon System, Defense Item, or Service Subject to Offset; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Names/Titles of Signatories to the Offset Agreement; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Value of Export Sale Subject to Offset (approximate); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Total Value of the Offset Agreement; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Term of Offset Agreement (months); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Description of Performance Measures_(e.g., ``Best Efforts,'' Liquidated Damages, (describe)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) For the first reporting period only, U.S. firms will be asked to provide this information for all offset agreements
currently in the fulfillment process (i.e., those with uncompleted offset obligations). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

