for the Paragraph (e) exception. As a result, absent an exemption from Rule 10b&hyph;6, issuers and other distribution
participants are required to comply with Rule 10b&hyph;6. Even with respect to plans that qualify for the Paragraph
(e) exception, the more recent use of such plans to broadly distribute the issuer's securities may not have been contemplated
by the Commission when Paragraph (e) was adopted. 
