<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Should the ``right to purchase'' concept be retained, or should it be replaced with a ``price-related security''
concept that would include all securities having a significant price relationship with the security in distribution?
Commenters favoring such an approach should address how ``price-related securities'' should be defined and how
to exclude securities or other instruments whose prices have a highly attenuated economic relationship to and, therefore,
