with short sales, because they have access to a pool of securities obtainable from distribution participants at a
fixed, and generally lower, price. It is this lower risk that can provide an incentive for manipulative short selling.
The Commission adopted Rule 10b&hyph;21 in 1988 to prohibit this type of short selling and covering.
