<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Although the general prohibition against an industry 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
member imposing conditions on receipt of items allowed in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart D has been removed from &sect;6.81, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed &sect;6.83 states that giving or selling 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
product displays may be conditioned upon the purchase of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the distilled spirits, wine or malt beverage product advertised 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
thereon in a quantity only necessary for the initial completion 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or use of the product display. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loan or rental of product displays would not be within 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the exception. Such a continuing tie would not be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consistent with the intent of the Act. Industry members 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
have long argued that they should be allowed to condition 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
receipt of product displays on the purchase of a limited 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
quantity of the product advertised. The dollar limit of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
$500 per brand, coupled with the requirements for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
permanently inscribed advertising and transfer of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ownership of product displays to the retailer minimizes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the inducement value to the retailer. The combination of these 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
factors allows product displays to be excepted from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the regulations of Part 6, and would be the basis for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
allowing the industry member to condition receipt of such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
materials as described above. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.84, Point of Sale Advertising and Consumer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Advertising Specialties 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Promotions and practices currently allowed under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulatory exceptions to the tied-house provisions are safe 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
harbors. This notice proposes a revision to those exceptions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which would combine several of the current exceptions into one 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
general regulatory section. The approach of having a single 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
general section addressing all of the similar activities gives 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
greater flexibility to the industry. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed regulations combine the exceptions listed in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;&sect;6.84, 6.85, 6.86 and 6.87, (inside signs, retailer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
advertising specialties, wine lists and consumer advertising 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specialties) into a revised &sect;6.84, Point of sale 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
advertising and consumer advertising specialties. Items 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
intended for consumers currently identified in &sect;6.47 are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
also included in the proposed listing of exceptions. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
petitioners requested that ATF amend the dollar limitation to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reflect the adjusted rates, but instead, under ATF's proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
revision there will be no limit to the specified point of sale 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(POS) materials furnished by an industry member to a retail 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establishment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The petitioners also requested that the term ``wine lists'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be expanded to include all alcoholic beverages. Instead, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed &sect;6.84 permits all lists or menus, subject to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
conditions in paragraph (c) of the section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.86, Temporary Retailers 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
ATF proposes adding a new section which will allow 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
furnishing things of value to a temporary retailer. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.88, Glassware_Section 6.89, Tapping Accessories_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 6.90, Supplies_Section 6.97, Coil Cleaning Service 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The petitioners recommend that these four sections be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
combined in a new section 6.88, under the title ``Equipment and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supplies,'' because they deal with similar types of merchandise 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and impose similar conditions. As with other subpart D 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exceptions which combine similar types of merchandise, (viz., 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;&sect;6.83, 6.87 and 6.89), the petitioners feel that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
combining these items in one section will enhance the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
simplicity and clarity of the rules. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The petitioners also recommend several other revisions to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this consolidated section. They believe that the coverage of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the coil cleaning service should be extended from ``a retailer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of wine or malt beverages'' to ``a retailer.'' This amendment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would provide equal treatment for wine, malt beverages and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
distilled spirits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The petitioners also recommend substituting the term 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``dispensing accessories'' in section 6.88 for ``tapping 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accessories'' because the former term more accurately describes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the modern type of accessories falling within this category and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reflects present marketplace practices where, for example, wine 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
also is served by dispensing equipment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The petitioners also feel that cold plates should be added 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to the list of examples of ``dispensing accessories'' and, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the present requirements for glassware and tapping 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accessories, carbon dioxide gas or ice may be sold at a price 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
not less than the cost to the industry member who initially 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purchased it. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The petitioners' proposed &sect;6.88 would read as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
follows: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
``&sect;6.88 Equipment and supplies. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Definition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Equipment and supplies means glassware, dispensing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accessories, carbon dioxide gas or ice. Dispensing accessories 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include items such as standards, faucets, cold plates, rods, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
vents, taps, tap standards, hoses, washers, couplings, gas 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gauges, vent tongues, shanks and check valves. (b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Application. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) An industry member may sell equipment or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supplies to a retailer if the equipment or supplies are sold at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a price not less than the cost to the industry member who 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
initially purchased it, and if the price is collected within 30 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
days of the date of the sale. (2) If dispensing accessories 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are sold pursuant to (1), the industry member also may install 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
them at the retailer's establishment. (c) Coil cleaning 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
service may be furnished, given or sold to a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
retailer.'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
While the petitioners' proposal to combine various 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sections into one all inclusive section covering equipment and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supplies is structurally logical and the terminology change 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
from tapping equipment to dispensing equipment has merit, some 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the items listed in the proposed section have not in the 
