<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Act makes applicable the provisions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including penalties of sections 49 and 50 of title 15, United 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
States Code, to the jurisdiction, powers and duties of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Director under this Act, and to any person (whether or not a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
corporation) subject to the provisions of law administered by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Director under this Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Examination and subpoena. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Director or any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
authorized ATF officers shall at all reasonable times have 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
access to, for the purpose of examination, and the right to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
copy any documentary evidence of any person, partnership, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
corporation being investigated or proceeded against; and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Director shall have the power to require by subpoena the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
attendance and testimony of witnesses and the production of all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
such documentary evidence relating to any matter under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
investigation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Reports required by the regional director 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(compliance).
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(l) 
