<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.96 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Consumer promotions.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Coupons. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The act by an industry member of furnishing to consumers coupons which are redeemable at a retail establishment does
not constitute a means to induce within the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act, provided the following conditions
are met: (1) Redemption of such coupons may not be limited to a particular retailer or group of retailers; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) An industry member may not reimburse a retailer for more than the face value of all coupons redeemed, plus a usual
and customary handling fee for the redemption of coupons.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=37 g=1 f=1 -->
* * * * *
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par. 35. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.97 is removed and reserved.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par. 36. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.98 is revised to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.98 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Advertising service.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The listing of the names and addresses of two or more retailers selling the products of an industry member in an advertisement
of that industry member does not constitute a means to induce within the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act, provided:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) The advertisement does not also contain the retail price of the product (except where the exclusive retailer in
the jurisdiction is a State or local agency), and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The listing is the only reference to the retailers in the advertisement and is relatively inconspicuous in relation
to the advertisement as a whole, and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The advertisement does not refer only to one retailer or only to retail establishments controlled directly or
indirectly by the same retailer, except where the retailer is an agency of a State or a political subdivision of a State.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par 37. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.99 is revised to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.99 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Stocking, rotation, and pricing service.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Industry members may, at a retail establishment, stock, rotate and affix the price to distilled spirits, wine, or
malt beverages which they sell, provided products of other industry members are not altered or disturbed. The rearranging
or resetting of all or part of a store or liquor department is not hereby authorized.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Shelf plan and shelf schematics. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The act by an industry member of providing a recommended shelf plan or shelf schematic for distilled spirits, wine,
or malt beverages does not constitute a means to induce within the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par 38. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.100 is revised to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.100 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Participation in retailer association activities.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The following acts by an industry member participating in retailer association activities do not constitute a means
to induce within the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Displaying its products at a convention or trade show,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Renting display booth space if the rental fee is the same as paid by all exhibitors at the event,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Providing its own hospitality which is independent from association sponsored activities,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Purchasing tickets to functions and paying registration fees if the payments or fees are the same as paid by all
exhibitors at the event, and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Making payments for advertisements in programs or brochures issued by retailer associations at a convention
or trade show if the total payments made by an industry member for all such advertisements do not exceed $500 per year
for any retailer association.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par. 39. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 6.101 is revised to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.101 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Merchandise.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The act by an industry member, who is also in business as a bona fide vendor of other merchandise (for example, groceries
or pharmaceuticals), of selling that merchandise to a retailer does not constitute a means to induce within the meaning
of section 105(b)(3) of the Act, provided:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The merchandise is sold at its fair market value, and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The merchandise is not sold in combination with distilled spirits, wines, or malt beverages, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The industry member's acquisition costs of the merchandise appears on the industry member's purchase invoices
or other records, and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Merchandise and distilled spirits, wines, or malt beverages sold in a single transaction are itemized separately
on the same invoice covering the sales transaction.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Things of value covered in other sections of this part. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The act by an industry member of providing equipment, fixtures, signs, glassware, supplies, services, and advertising
specialties to retailers does not constitute a means to induce within the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act only
as provided in other sections within this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par. 40. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A new &sect;6.102 is added to subpart D to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;6.102 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Outside signs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The act by an industry member of furnishing outside signs to a retailer does not constitute a means to induce within
the meaning of section 105(b)(3) of the Act provided that:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The retailer is not compensated, directly or indirectly such as through a sign company, for displaying the signs,
and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The cost of the signs may not exceed $500.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Par. 41. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Part 6 is amended by adding a new subpart E to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=72 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart E_Exclusion
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=26 g=1 f=1 -->
6.151&blank;Exclusion, in general.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
6.152&blank;Practices which put retailer independence at risk.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
6.153&blank;Criteria for determining retailer independence.
