<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
</FOOTNOTE>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) The following general policies apply to processing of 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
debt complaints.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Creditors are encouraged to use the processing procedures for debt complaints described in appendix A to this
part. Complaints meeting the requirements of this part will receive prompt processing assistance from commanders.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Assistance in indebtedness matters will not be extended to those creditors:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Who have not made a bona fide effort to collect the debt directly from the military member;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Whose claims are patently false and misleading;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Whose claims are obviously exorbitant; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Who are in an ``off-limits'' status, or who have been determined to be practicing unfair consumer or commercial
practices detrimental to the morale and welfare of service members, pursuant to applicable directives of the military
services, to include the Armed Forces Disciplinary Control Board and Off-Installation Liaison and Operations regulations.
<FOOTCITE>6</FOOTCITE>

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<FOOTNOTE>
<FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=3 -->
6
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

</FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=3 -->
See footnote 1 to &sect;50.4(c).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
</FOOTNOTE>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
(3) Some States have enacted laws which prohibit creditors from contacting a debtor's employer with respect to indebtedness
or communicating facts on indebtedness to an employer unless certain conditions are met. The conditions which must
be met to remove this prohibition are generally such things as reduction of a debt to judgment and obtaining written
permission of the debtor.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) At DoD installations in States having such laws, the processing of debt complaints will not be extended to those
creditors who are in violation of the State law. Commanders may advise creditors that this rule has been established
because it is the general policy of the Military Services to comply with State law when that law does not infringe upon
significant military interests.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) This policy will govern even though a creditor is not licensed to do business in the State where the debtor is located.
A similar practice will be commenced in any State enacting a similar law with respect to debt collection.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Under the provisions of Public Law 95&hyph;109, contact by a debt collector with third parties, such as commanding
officers, for the purpose of aiding debt collection is prohibited without a court order, or the debtor's prior consent,
given directly to the debt collector. Creditors are generally exempt from Public Law 95&hyph;109, but only when they
collect on their own behalf. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The following general policies apply to processing of involuntary allotments (except statutory allotments
for child support or alimony).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

