<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
I. Background
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
A. Overview of Title I Scheme
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The OTC's recommendation under section 184(c) of the Act that EPA mandate that States in the OTR adopt the LEV program
arises in the context of the program designed to address ozone (or ``smog'') pollution in subpart II of part D of title
I of the Act. This program is described in detail in EPA's General Preamble for the Implementation of Title I of the Clean
Air Act Amendments of 1990, 57 FR 13498 (April 16, 1992), and the Nitrogen Oxides Supplement to the General Preamble,
57 FR 55620 (Nov. 25, 1992).
