<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 184(c) specifies a procedure for the OTC to develop 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recommendations for additional control measures to be applied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
within all or a part of the OTR if the OTC determines that such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measures are necessary to bring any area in the OTR into 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
attainment for ozone by the applicable dates in the Act. Section 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
184(c)(1) provides that Upon petition of any States within a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
transport region for ozone, and based on a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
majority vote of the Governors on the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Commission (or their designees), the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Commission may, after notice and opportunity 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for public comment, develop recommendations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for additional control measures to be applied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
within all or a part of such transport region 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
if the commission determines such measures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are necessary to bring any area in such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
region into attainment by the dates provided 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by [subpart II of part D of title I of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Clean Air Act]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 184(c) also lays out procedures the Administrator is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to follow in responding to recommendations from the OTC. Upon 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
receipt of the recommendations, the Administrator is to publish a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 notice stating that the recommendations are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
available and providing an opportunity for a public hearing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
within 90 days. On March 18, 1994, EPA published a notice 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
announcing receipt of the OTC recommendation, 59 FR 12914. EPA 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
further announced on April 8, 1994 that a public hearing would be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
held in Hartford, Connecticut on May 2&hyph;3, 1994, 59 FR 16811 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(April 8, 1994). The Administrator is also to ``commence a review 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the recommendations to determine whether the control measures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the recommendations are necessary to bring any area in such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
region into attainment by the dates provided by [subpart II] and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are otherwise consistent with [the] Act.'' Finally, in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
undertaking her review, the Administrator is to consult with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
members of the OTC and is to take into account the data, views, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and comments received pursuant to the public hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Last, sections 184(c) (4) and (5) govern EPA's response to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the OTC recommendations. The Administrator is to determine 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether to approve, disapprove, or partially approve and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
partially disapprove the recommendations within nine months of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
receipt. For any disapproval, the Administrator is to specify: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Why any disapproved additional control measures are not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
necessary to bring any area in such region into attainment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by the dates provided by [subpart II] or are otherwise not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consistent with the Act; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Recommendations concerning equal or more effective 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
actions that could be taken by the commission to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
conform the disapproved portion of the recommendations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to the requirements of [section 184]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 184(c)(5) provides that, upon approval or partial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approval of any recommendations, the Administrator is to issue to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
each State in the OTR to which an approved requirement applies a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
finding under section 110(k)(5) that the SIP for that State is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
inadequate to meet the requirements of section 110(a)(2)(D), 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
quoted above. Under section 184(c)(5), the Administrator's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
finding of inadequacy under section 110(a)(2)(D) is to require 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that each affected State revise its SIP to include the approved 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
additional control measures within one year after the finding is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
issued. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Finally, section 184(d) provides that, for purposes of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section 184, the Administrator is to ``promulgate criteria for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purposes of determining the contribution of sources in one area 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to concentrations of ozone'' in another nonattainment area. These 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
criteria are to ``require that the best available air quality 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring and modeling techniques be used for purposes of making 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
such determinations.'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
C. Background Regarding OTC LEV Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Administrator convened the OTC on May 7, 1991. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Thereafter, the OTC moved to work toward a regional ozone 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
strategy with emphasis on consensus agreements to adopt regional 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measures to address the ozone problem in the Northeast. To 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
address the contribution of motor vehicles to the Northeast ozone 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
problem, the OTC focussed early on emissions standards for new 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
motor vehicles and on adoption of federal reformulated gasoline 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
throughout the OTR as potential additional control measures. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Act, however, imposes certain limitations on the States' ability 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to adopt new motor vehicle emissions standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

