<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 209 of the Act generally preempts States from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establishing new motor vehicle emissions standards, leaving such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulation to EPA under section 202 of the Act. Section 209 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
does, however, provide an exception for California to adopt new 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
motor vehicle emissions standards where the Administrator grants 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a preemption waiver based on a finding that California's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standards will be, ``in the aggregate, at least as protective of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
public health and welfare as applicable Federal standards.'' 
