SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 EPA is proposing to approve revisions to the State Implementation Plan (SIP) submitted by the State of Florida through
the Florida Department of Environmental Protection (FDEP) for the purpose of establishing a Small Business Stationary
Source Technical and Environmental Compliance Assistance Program (PROGRAM), which will be fully implemented by
November 1994. This implementation plan was submitted by FDEP on February 24, 1993, to satisfy the federal mandate,
found in section 507 of the Clean Air Act as amended in 1990 (CAA), to ensure that small businesses have access to the
technical assistance and regulatory information necessary to comply with the CAA.
