</FOOTNOTE>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposals made today with respect to these separate financial statements are based on the recognition that U.S.
companies may have the same difficulties in, and costs, of obtaining reconciled financial statements for foreign
acquisitions and foreign investments as foreign issuers for whom the Commission adopted revisions to the requirements
today.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
A. Significant Threshold for Equity Investees
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Commission is proposing to modify one of the three tests for significance made pursuant to Rule 3&hyph;09 of Regulation
S&hyph;X to determine whether financial statements of an equity investee, foreign or domestic, must be provided.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
23
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Commission believes that, for purposes of this rule, the significance of an investee should be based on a comparison
of the registrant's proportionate share of the investee's pre-tax income to that of the registrant and of the registrant's
investment in the investee relative to the registrant's total assets. Comparison of the investee's total assets
to the total assets of the registrant, as presently required, appears insufficiently relevant if the investee is
less than majority owned and, therefore, its financial statements are not consolidated in the registrant's financial
statements. Accordingly, the Commission proposes to amend Rule 3&hyph;09 of Regulation S&hyph;X to eliminate the
requirement to consider total assets of a less than majority owned investee in the evaluation of its significance.
Comment is requested as to whether the asset test should be eliminated.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

