<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The following definitions apply to this part:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Act
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 and 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
OAA
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 mean the Older Americans Act of 1965, as amended (42 U.S.C. 3001, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
.).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Area agency on aging
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an area agency on aging designated under section 305(a)(2)(A) of the Act or a State agency performing the functions
of an area agency on aging under section 305(b)(5) of the Act.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Authorized position
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an enrollment opportunity during a program year. The number of authorized positions is derived by dividing
the total amount of funds appropriated during a program year by the national average unit cost per enrollee for that
program year as determined by the Department. The national average unit cost includes all administration costs,
other enrollee costs, and enrollee wage and fringe benefit costs. An allotment of the total dollars for the recipient
is divided by the national unit cost to determine the total number of authorized positions for each grant agreement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Community service
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means social, health, welfare, and educational services (particularly literacy tutoring); legal assistance,
and other counseling services, including tax counseling and assistance and financial counseling; library, recreational,
day care and other similar services; conservation, maintenance, or restoration of natural resources; community
betterment or beautification; pollution control and environmental quality efforts; weatherization activities;
and includes inter-generational projects; but is not limited to the above. It excludes building and highway construction
(except that which normally is performed by the project sponsor) and work which primarily benefits private, profit-making
organizations. [Section 507(2).]
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Department
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 and 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
DOL
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 mean the United States Department of Labor, including its agencies and organizational units.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Disability
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a physical or mental impairment of an individual that substantially limits one or more major life activities;
a record of such impairment; or being regarded as having such an impairment. [29 CFR parts 32 and 34.]
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Dual eligibility
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the status of those eligible individuals who satisfy the eligibility requirements of section 203 of the JTPA
and/or title V of the OAA. In programs carried out jointly with JTPA, Title V eligible individuals shall be deemed to
satisfy the requirements of section 203 of the JTPA. To be recognized as a program for which dual eligibility may be
established, the JTPA service delivery area and the title V recipient or subrecipient must establish a written financial
or non-financial agreement to carry out joint programs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Eligible individual
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a person who is 55 years of age, or older, and who has a low income as defined in this section. [Section 507(1).]
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

