<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.308
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Orientation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Enrollee. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
After an individual enrolls in a community service employment assignment, the recipient or subrecipient shall,
as soon as practicable, provide orientation to the enrollee. The orientation shall provide, as appropriate, information
related to: project objectives; community service employment assignments; training; supportive services; responsibilities,
rights, and duties of the enrollee; permitted and prohibited political activities; plans to transition to unsubsidized
employment and a discussion of safe working conditions at the host agencies.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Host agency.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The recipient or a subrecipient shall provide to those individuals who will supervise enrollees at the host agencies,
the orientation described in paragraph (a) of this section. This is to assure that enrollees will receive adequate
supervision and opportunities for transitioning to the host agency staff or other unsubsidized employment.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Supevision.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The recipient or subrecipient shall ensure that host agencies provide adequate orientation, instruction, and supervision
for enrollees job responsibilities regarding responsibilities and safety.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

