<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(5) Shall not employ or continue to employ any enrollee to perform work which is the same or substantially the same as
that performed by any other person who is on layoff. [Section 502(b)(1)(G).]
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.326 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Experimental private sector training projects.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Department may authorize a recipient to develop an experimental job training project(s) designed to provide
second career training and the placement of eligible individuals in employment opportunities with private business
concerns. [Section 502(e).]
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Experimental project agreements for training may be with States, public agencies, non-profit private organizations,
and private business concerns.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The geographic location of these projects shall be determined by the Department to insure an equitable distribution
of such projects.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) To the extent feasible, experimental projects shall emphasize second-career training, innovative work modes,
including those with reduced physical exertion, and placement into growth industries and jobs reflecting new technologies.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The Department shall establish by administrative guidelines, the application schedule, content, format, allocation
levels and reporting requirements for experimental projects.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) Current title V eligibility standards shall be used for experimental projects, unless the Department permits,
in writing, the use of another approved income index.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) Projects funded under section 502(e) of the Act shall seek to be coordinated with projects carried out under section
204(d) of the JTPA to the extent feasible.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) Recipients shall distribute funds for experimental projects in accordance with the State allocation formulas
in their title V grant.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=56 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart D_Administrative Standards and Procedures for Recipient and Limitations on Federal Funds
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.401 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
General.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This subpart establishes limitations on title V funds to be used for community service activities and describes,
or incorporates by reference, requirements for the administration of grants by recipient of SCSEP.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.402 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Administrative requirements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Except as otherwise provided in this part, title V funds shall be administered in accordance with, and subject
to, the Department's regulations at 29 CFR parts 31, 32, 34, 93, 96, and 98. In addition, projects and activities administered
by State, local or Indian tribal governments are also subject to the Department's administrative requirements regulations
at 29 CFR part 97; projects and activities administered by institutions of higher education, hospitals, or other
non-profit organizations are subject to the Department's administrative requirements regulations at 41 CFR part
29&hyph;70 (1984). Recipients of title V funds shall be subject to any revisions of any implementing regulations
cited in this paragraph (a) on the effective date of such revisions.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The administration of interagency agreements set forth in subpart E of this part is not subject to paragraph (a)
of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.403 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allowable costs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Costs shall be determined in accordance with the cost principles indicated in paragraph (b) of this section, except
as otherwise provided in this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicable Cost Principles. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The cost principles set forth in paragraphs (b) (1) through (4) of this section apply to the organization incurring
the costs:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) OMB Circular A&hyph;87_State, local or Indian tribal government;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) OMB Circular A&hyph;122_Private, non-profit organization other than:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Institution of higher education;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Hospital; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Other organization named in OMB Circular A&hyph;122 as not subject to OMB Circular A&hyph;122;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) OMB Circular A&hyph;21_Educational institution; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940426-1-00155 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940426-1-00018 </PARENT>
