<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(4) 48 CFR Part 31.2_Commercial organization (for-profit organization, other than a hospital or other organization
name in OMB Circular A&hyph;122 as not subject to OMB Circular A&hyph;122).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Lobbying costs.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 In addition to the prohibition contained in 29 CFR part 93 and in accordance with limitations on the use of appropriated
funds in Department of Labor Appropriation Acts, title V funds shall not be used to pay any salaries or expenses related
to any activity designed to influence legislation or appropriations pending before the Congress of the United States.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Building repairs and acquisition costs.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 No Federal grant funds provided to a recipient or subrecipient under title V or this part may be expended directly or
indirectly for the purchase, erection, or repair of any building except for the labor involved in:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Minor remodeling of a public building necessary to make it suitable for use by project administrators;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Minor repair and rehabilitation of publicly used facilities for the general benefit of the community; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Minor repair and rehabilitation by enrollees of housing occupied by persons with low incomes who are declared
eligible for such services by authorized local agencies.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Allowable fringe benefit costs.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The cost of the following fringe benefits are allowable: initial and annual physical assessments, annual leave,
sick leave, holidays, health insurance, social security, workman's compensation and any other fringe benefits
approved in the grant agreement and permitted by the appropriate Federal cost principles found in OMB Circular A&hyph;87
and A&hyph;122, except as limited by &sect;641.311(c).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.404
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Classification of costs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
All costs must be charged to one of the following three cost categories:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Administration.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The cost category of Administration shall include, but need not be limited to, the direct and indirect costs of providing:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Administration, management, and direction of a program or project;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Reports on evaluation, management, community benefits, and other aspects of project activity;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Assistance of an advisory council, if any;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Accounting and management information systems;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Training and technical assistance for recipient or subrecipient staff;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Bonding; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Audits.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Enrollee wages and fringe benefits.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The cost category of Enrollee Wages and Fringe Benefits shall include wages paid to enrollees for hours of community
service assignments as described in &sect;641.311 or training as described in &sect;641.313, and the costs of fringe
benefits provided in accordance with &sect;641.311.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
