(b) No subgrant or other subagreement may provide for any expenditure of funds beyond the ending date of the grant agreement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) For purposes of this part, procurement, as described in 29 CFR part 97 and 41 CFR 29&hyph;70.216 (1984), does not
include the award or administration of subgrant agreements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.411 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Program income accountability.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any of the methods described at 29 CFR 97.25 or 41 CFR 29&hyph;70.205 (1984), as appropriate, may be used to account
for program income.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.412 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Equipment.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Equipment purchased by a State recipient with title V funds prior to July 1, 1989, shall be subject to 29 CFR 97.32.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.413 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Audits.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each recipient is responsible for complying with the Single Audit Act of 1984 (31 U.S.C. 7501, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) and 29 CFR part 96, the Department of Labor regulation which implements Office of Management and Budget Circular
A&hyph;128, ``Audits of State and Local Governments''; or OMB Circular 133, ``Audits of Institutions of Higher Education
and Other Nonprofit Institutions'', as appropriate.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.414 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Grant closeout procedures.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Grant closeout procedures for title V grants to State, local, or Indian tribal governments shall conform to the requirements
at 29 CFR 97.50. As necessary, the Department shall issue supplementary closeout instructions for all title V recipients,
including recipients not subject to 29 CFR part 97.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;641.415 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Department of Labor appeals procedures for recipients.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) This section sets forth the procedures by which recipient may appeal a SCSEP final determination by the Department
relating to costs, payments, notices of suspension, and notices of termination other than those resulting from an
audit. Appeals of suspensions and terminations for discrimination shall be processed under 29 CFR part 31, 32, or
34, as appropriate.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Appeals from a final disallowance of cost as a result of an audit shall be made pursuant to 29 CFR subpart 96.6.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Upon a recipient's receipt of the Department's final determination relating to costs (except final disallowance
of cost as a result of an audit), payments, suspension or termination, the recipient may appeal the final determination
to the Department's Office of Administrative Law Judges, as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Within 21 days of receipt of the Department's final determination, the recipient may transmit by certified mail,
return receipt requested, a request for a hearing to the Chief Administrative Law Judge, United States Department
of Labor, 800 K Street, N.W., room 400N, Washington, D.C. 20001 with a copy to Department official who signed the final
determination. The Chief Administrative Law Judge shall designate an administrative law judge to hear the appeal.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The request for hearing shall be accompanied by a copy of the final determination, if issued, and shall state specifically
those issues of the determination upon which review is requested. Those provisions of the determination not specified
for review, or the entire determination when no hearing has been requested, shall be considered resolved and not subject
to further review.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Rules of Practice and Procedures for Administrative Hearings Before the Office of Administrative Law Judges, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
set forth at 29 CFR part 18, shall govern the conduct of hearings under this section, except that:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The appeal shall not be considered a complaint; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Technical rules of evidence, such as the Federal Rules of Evidence and subpart B of 29 CFR part 18, shall not apply
to any hearing conducted pursuant to this section. However, rules designed to assure production of the most credible
evidence available and to subject testimony to test by cross-examination shall be applied where reasonably necessary
by the administrative law judge conducting the hearing. The certified copy of the administrative file transmitted
to the administrative law judge by the official issuing the final determination shall be part of the evidentiary record
of the case and need not be moved into evidence.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
